  "text": "Identification of the roles of conserved charged residues in the extracellular domain of an epithelial sodium channel (ENaC) subunit by alanine mutagenesis EPITHELIAL SODIUM CHANNELS (ENaC) are located at the apical membrane of epithelial cells where their major function is to funnel Na ϩ ions from the lumen into the cell. Sodium ions that enter the epithelial cells via ENaC are then pumped out into the interstitial space via Na-K-ATPase located on the opposite basolateral membrane [CITATION_1] .",
